# Project Memory

This project maintains a `memory/` folder at the workspace root. **Always read these files before asking the user for context about the project.**

## Memory Files

| File | Contains |
|------|---------|
| `memory/project-brief.md` | Brand identity, target audience, CTAs, conversion goals |
| `memory/design-tokens.md` | Full color palette, typography scale, component classes |
| `memory/architecture.md` | File structure, dependency map, component inventory |

## Reading Priority

When starting a task:

1. Check if the task is in `memory/` — read the relevant file
2. If not found, use Grep/Glob to search the codebase
3. Only ask the user if both above fail

## Updating Memory

After completing a task that changes structure or tokens:

```
memory/architecture.md  → new/removed components, new dependencies
memory/design-tokens.md → new color tokens, new CSS classes
memory/project-brief.md → copy changes, new CTA targets, brand updates
```

Keep each memory file **under 200 lines**. If it grows larger, split into sub-files (e.g. `memory/components/*.md`).
